Java static block or static initializer block is the group of statements that gets executed when the class is loaded  by Java class loader.

So a static block is executed even before main method. 

Static block is used to initialize static variables of the class. 

A class can have multiple static blocks which are executed in the same order they are defined in the class. 

e.g.
   class A{
